Validation scripts for BHMM.

DESCRIPTION

These scripts generate data from a model system and test whether the confidence intervals generated by sampling from the posterior reproduce the expected confidence intervals of the model.

MANIFEST

test_confidence_intervals.m - run tests with fixed parameter three state model
plot_confidence_intervals.m - generate confidence interval validation plots

generate_test_model.m - generate both model and synthetic data with fixed parameters
generate_problematic_test_model.m - generate a challenging model and synthetic data that can give EM Gaussian mixture initialization trouble
generate_random_test_model.m - generate both model and synthetic data with random parameters

generate_synthetic_data.m - generate synthetic observation data from a given model

three_state_model.m - generate three-state model with fixed parameters
four_state_model.m - generate four-state test model with fixed parameters

beta_confidence_intervals.m - estimate confidence intervals and uncertainties
empirical_confidence_interval.m - estimate confidence interval using a finite sample

EXPERIMENTAL

generate_problematic_test_model.m - generate especially difficult test models where two states overlap to a large degree

